HEADWORD: Mummify
<hw>Mum"mi*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Mummified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Mummifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[<ets>Mummy</ets> + <ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>momifier</ets>.]</ety> <def>To embalm and dry as a mummy; to make
into, or like, a mummy.</def> <rj><au>Hall (1646).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

